{
  "stem": "12289.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then Wallenberg told her that, if you cooperate now and convince your husband that he has to announce that, after all, these passport are still valid, I will do my best to see to it that your husband, after the war, won't be accused of being a-- a war criminal.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That I-- I'll try to help safe him-- save him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, Raoul Wallenberg could never do that, because he was, himself, deported by the-- by the Soviets.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he couldn't help this-- this Kemeny was his name, Baron Kemeny.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyhow, she-- she convinced her husband to go to the radio and declare these passports valid, which he did.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so for the moment, we managed, through-- through Raoul Wallenberg's ingenuity, to save the situation for a while.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what-- what date approximately was it?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In what--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it could have been-- it could have been a rather early stage.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It could have been at the, say, at the end of-- at the end of October or something, '44.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were on the-- we were bombed, of course, the whole time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- I didn't-- I didn't see it, because we-- we were never part of a battle in the-- on the Buda side, between the Germans and the-- the Russian-- and the Soviets.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I guess that Wallenberg, who stayed on-- on the Pest side, and those people there, that was the fighting, house by house, like that, how the-- the Soviets-- the Soviets' army entered the city, big, heavy fightings.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the Buda side, they-- they managed to get in without any fightings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they were good.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They-- they made a trap for the garrison in Buda to-- to try to get out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they managed.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
